9:
Shouldn't you be used to these
sandy sights, considering you're
from these parts?
13:
Tsk, tsk, Alk! It's all about the thrill of
the moment, you know? I'm not here
on business for once!
17:
Plus I'm rocking a brand new
swimsuit! It'd be weirder if I wasn't
over the moon!
22:
You're wearing a different swimsuit
than the one you showed me in
Starview.
25:
Oh, nice of you to notice! I won this
in an amusement park game!
28:
I knew I had to have it the moment I
laid eyes on it! Picked it up for
myself just yesterday.
32:
I believe I saw a similar game in the
resort. I would like to try it sometime.
38:
Hold it, Stella! You'd better be
prepared to lose EVERYTHING if you
start down that path!
42:
Yeah, the risk is definitely not worth
the reward in this case...
46:
Oh, come on... I promise not
everyone's out to scam the newbies!
51:
You expect us to trust the word of
someone who takes bets off the
street?
56:
What's there to worry about? Are
you really going to crush Stella's
dreams? She's raring to go, so I say
we go!
60:
Okay, so I know I said there wasn't
anything to worry about, but there
ARE a couple rules to keep in mind.
62:
Don't go head-to-head with other
patrons. Only play against official
staff.
63:
If you encounter anything fishy,
report it to the staff. Sometimes
some real shady stuff happens
while nobody's looking.
68:
Uh, hello? What part of that screams
"nothing to worry about"?!
71:
Like I said, you can relax! Just get
the employees to handle any
trouble that comes up.
74:
Oh yeah, one last thing! This is the
most important part—don't tunnel
vision!
75:
Take your loss with grace and back
out before you lose everything.
Nimbus, I want you especially to
watch yourself.
80:
That's rich comin' from the likes of
you.
84:
Listen. I promise I'll bail you guys out
if you get into a pickle.
89:
Oh come on, Alk! You're more
adventurous than this! Have some
fun, go all in!
93:
Nimbus? Niiiimbus?
Okay, that's enough for you.
99:
Hehe, are you quite sure? I hope
you're prepared for a challenge.
105:
Onto the next round. You'll be joining
me, yes?
107: Of course. I won't lose this time.
112: Stella! What'd I say about losing?!
115:
Hey, mister. Mind if I sub in for my
girl here?
117: A friend, I gather? Go right ahead.
120:
Thanks! Before we get started
though—
123:
No more of that pathetic cheating,
okay? It's embarrassing!
129:
What? Planning on hightailing it?
You're no fun.
132:
Bet that works out nicely for YOU,
dealer.
133:
Imagine what would happen if word
got out that you didn't notice such
blatant cheating.
138:
I'm all in next round. You can add
my friend's chips to mine.
140:
If you win, you get everything, plus I'll
let your cheating slide. How about
it? Still going to scamper away?
142: Oh, you're going to regret this!
146:
All or nothing. How do you like our
odds, Stella?
152:
What about you? Last chance to
back out.
158:
That's what I like to hear! Life's too
short not to have some fun!
162:
Four of a kind! Read 'em and weep!
Did you really think I only had one
trick—
164:
Is that all?
Enjoy this royal straight flush.
171:
You know, those tricks of yours work
better in a circus than a casino.
181:
By the way, you had one heck of a
poker face. Maybe we can make a
gambler out of you yet.
182: How about it? Want to learn?
